== Technical specification II ==

{| class="wikitable sortable" style="text-align: center; font-size: 85%; width: 100%; table-layout: fixed;"

|-
! style="width: 12em; text-align: left" | Name
! Converters for
! Probability calculation functions<ref name="probcalc">Provides the facility to calculate probability mass (or density), cumulative probability, moments, etc. of a distribution directly in the spreadsheet.</ref>
! [[User-defined function|UDF]] error analysis<ref name="error">Standard error messages like #VALUE! when an input parameter is invalid is replaced by a message describing the reason of the error.</ref>
! Extreme value modeling<ref name="extreme">Tools to evaluate the distribution of the minimum or maximum sample from a set of [[Independent and identically distributed random variables|IIDs]]</ref>
! Expert elicitation tools<ref name="expert">Graphical interfaces to facilitate determining distribution of uncertainty of some model parameter based on expert opinion.</ref>
! Data previsualizer
! [[Ordinary differential equation|ODE]] and [[numerical integration]]
! Assumption library
